Hello @jwhui 

Unfortunately fix didn't help, although i have enough GDB information to know what happened.

The HardFault from above suggested that the content of `mMatchingAddress` field in Mpl class is overwritten. This varaible is above `mSeedSet`. So i've added additional asserts to check where this unwanted access takes place:

```
     if (evict > insert)
     {
+        assert((uint32_t)insert > (uint32_t)&mMatchingAddress);
         memmove(insert, insert + 1, static_cast<size_t>(evict - insert) * sizeof(MplSeedEntry));
     }
     else if (evict < insert)
     {
+        assert((uint32_t)evict > (uint32_t)&mMatchingAddress);
         memmove(evict, evict + 1, static_cast<size_t>(insert - 1 - evict) * sizeof(MplSeedEntry));
         insert--;
     }
```

I found out that in stress tests, the second assert is triggered. The issues is related with `curCount` value overflow (> 32).

