You should try running this with `double`.  Like always use `double` unless you specifically need `float`.  Using `float` here is going to cause most of the optimizer to run with `float` which could lead to slower convergence since `float` has much less precision than `double`.  Might not matter here though, IDK, but you should check and the default recommendation should be to use `double` unless memory is so tight `float` is specifically needed.  Like on the CPU, `float` isn't faster than `double` (in 99% of cases, and in many cases the numeric loss of `float` can make it slower).

